sentences: Me saame tulevaid uudiseid homme hommikul.
Järgmise nädala jooksul tuleb palju külalisi.
context: The word 'tulevad' is the plural form of the Estonian verb 'tulema', which means 'to come'. It describes something that is coming, approaching, or will happen in the future. This word often appears with nouns to indicate things that are expected to arrive or occur later.
